Africa Magic, a leading provider of premium African entertainment, will in January premiere the third season of hit drama series, “Unmarried”, and the reality TV series, “Date My Family Nigeria”. Dr Busola Tejumola, Executive Head, Content and West Africa Channels, MultiChoice Nigeria, made the disclosure in a statement in Lagos. According to the official, the popular comedy series, “My Siblings and I”, will return for a fourth season. After bringing together 13 beautiful couples in Season Two, the most immersive dating experience, “Date My Family’, is back with a bang for a third season. Tejumola said that lovers of the drama series should look forward to seeing 13 couples meet one another, go on a first date and possibly catch the love bug. - Advertisement - She said that the Season Four of “My siblings and I” would kick off on Jan. 10 on Africa Magic Urban.   Boy, 4, drowns in well in Kano     Rivers police investigate ‘mob attack’ on artiste     CP Odumosu, estate residents bicker over alleged entry…   “Unmarried” which follows the lives of three single women will premiere on Jan. 12 on Africa Magic Showcase. “ Fans will see favourite ladies, Funbi (Enado Odigie), Kamsi (Folu Storms), and Nengi (Venita Akpofure) return to their screens, following the Season Two finale cliffhanger,” she said. She said that in keeping with its commitment, MultiChoice had continued to create local content that kept viewers engaged and entertained. Tejumola said: “Local content is at the heart of our production at Africa Magic. “We continue to tell authentic Nigerian stories whilst showcasing the best entertainment content the continent has to offer. “The new seasons join other Africa Magic series – “Dilemma”, “Venge”, “Movement-Japa” and “The Rishantes”, giving viewers a more diverse range of local stories to watch.”   (NAN)